{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Bring provider configs under version control + repo-wide CLAUDE.md reference sweep\n\n## Why\n\nOnce `AGENTS.md` is canonical, two things must happen so the migration actually ships to other\nproviders and clones: (1) the scattered `CLAUDE.md` references across the committed tree must be\nupdated so nothing points at stale guidance, and (2) the provider-config scaffolding must be\n**committed** — a spike discovered that `.codex/config.toml` and `.agents/rules/rebar.md` exist\nonly as **untracked, locally `.git/info/exclude`d files on one machine** (`git ls-files` returns\nnothing for them), so today no other clone or provider sees them at all.\n\n## What\n\n- **Reference sweep:** update the ~15 committed files that name `CLAUDE.md` (CONTRIBUTING.md,\n  README.md, CHANGELOG.md, rebar.toml, and docs/{architecture,event-schema,exit-codes,\n  api-stability,jira-sync-setup,llm-framework,plan-review-criteria-guide,releasing,workflow-editor,\n  workflow-engine}.md, adr/0043) to the new AGENTS.md-canonical structure. The rename breaks zero\n  code (every `src/` hit is the unrelated `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` env var or a prose comment).\n- **Plan-review criteria text:** `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json` and\n  `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md` cite \"an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc\" in their\n  rubric — update to `AGENTS.md` so the gate's own coaching points at the new file.\n- **Commit the Codex config:** bring `.codex/config.toml` under version control (`git add -f`,\n  since it is currently locally excluded) with its content pointing at `AGENTS.md` and the\n  \"temporary…until migrated\" comment updated to the completed state.\n- **Commit the generic rules file:** bring `.agents/rules/rebar.md` under version control.\n  Default form: a concise distillation that **references `AGENTS.md`** as the source of truth\n  (Antigravity `.agents/rules/*` does not support `@`-imports, so a short reference-and-summary,\n  not a symlink).\n- **Per-tool pointers:** record the decision on optional `.github/copilot-instructions.md` /\n  `.cursor/rules` / Gemini config. Default: **defer to a follow-up ticket** (none added here); any\n  added later must be pointers to `AGENTS.md`, not duplicated content.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: the reference-sweep files, the two criteria files, `.codex/config.toml`, `.agents/rules/rebar.md`.\nOut: the root-file and template changes (their own stories). **Depends on S2 and S3** (already\nlinked): the sweep runs after `AGENTS.md` exists. Rollback: `git revert` — all edits are\ndocs/config/text with no data migration.\n\n## Assumption (flag for override)\n\nThe epic's goal (\"provider-generic guidance *available to* Codex/Cursor/Antigravity\") is only met\nif the provider configs are committed, so this story **brings `.codex/` and `.agents/` into\nversion control**. If the team instead wants provider configs to stay per-developer/local, drop\nthose two bullets and this story becomes the reference sweep + criteria-text update only.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] No un-updated `CLAUDE.md` reference remains in the committed surface; the only residual hits\n  are the intentional thin `CLAUDE.md` pointer file itself.\n  - Proving: `[ \"$(rg -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' --glob '!CLAUDE.md' --glob '!.rebar/**' --glob '!bridge_state/**' --glob '!docs/experiments/**' --glob '!.git/**' | awk -F: '{s+=$2} END{print s+0}')\" = 0 ]`\n- [ ] The plan-review criteria text references `AGENTS.md`, not `CLAUDE.md`.\n  - Proving: `[ \"$(rg -c 'CLAUDE\\.md' src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5e.md | awk -F: '{s+=$2} END{print s+0}')\" = 0 ]`\n- [ ] `.codex/config.toml` is git-tracked and points at `AGENTS.md`.\n  - Proving: `[ -n \"$(git ls-files .codex/config.toml)\" ] && rg -q 'AGENTS.md' .codex/config.toml`\n- [ ] `.agents/rules/rebar.md` is git-tracked and references `AGENTS.md` as the source of truth.\n  - Proving: `[ -n \"$(git ls-files .agents/rules/rebar.md)\" ] && rg -q 'AGENTS.md' .agents/rules/rebar.md`\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The per-tool-pointer decision (default: defer) is recorded as a comment\n  on this ticket citing the choice.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` pass and the module-size CI gate is green.\n  - Proving: `make lint && make test`"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784235337388650001,"uuid":"23438efb-15f5-472a-b0c2-65c85fc8be1c"}